data.title: Great place but arrive early.
data.text: I got here too late for breakfast and it was packed already for lunch, but did score a giant and delicious BLT for the road. I'll try to arrive earlier next time I guess.

data.title: Breakfast
data.text: This place is amazing!!!   We arrived at 730 am and the wait staff was delightful.  They brought the plates... I ordered a half of a plate and my friends ordered full plates they met their plates wig ahhhh!   Soooo great!!!

data.title: Great place to grab a bite!
data.text: My first time here! Met a friend for an early lunch,he has been coming here for years. Great service, clean restrooms, and very friendly staff. The food has really good flavor, and the portions are huge!

data.title: Large Portions, Not Bad Prices
data.text:
I went for lunch with a coworker. My coworker ordered a 1/2 sandwich that was HUGE. 
I ordered the "diet salad" with chicken salad. It was also very large. The chicken salad was good, but just average.

data.title: Don't miss having breakfast here!
data.text:
We love these people. This isn't just a restaurant, it's a family. It can get noisy and a little rushed, but it is all happy and worth any wait and hubbub. We take visitors here all the time, and we go when it is just the two of us.

The food is generous and very good. The banana bread is better than ANY! we have found in our travels. From French toast to plain oatmeal or sandwiches for lunch, we recommend it all. Five stars for any and all of it. 

They are only open for breakfast and lunch. They are closed Sunday and Monday. (There is no supper because the owner prioritized spending time at home with his family over making more money. Just sayin' . . .)

data.title: Big Breakfast
data.text: The best place in south King County for breakfast.  Famous for their muffins and banana bread.  Their lunch sandwiches are also great.  Whenever family comes to town we make a trip to Sun Break.  Closed Sunday & Monday.

data.title: WOW!
data.text: Fabulous breakfast, new choices not typically at other places.  Excellent service and I cannot stop talking about the banana    bread! OMG to die for!

data.title: Down home, country breakfast
data.text: Sun Break is our favorite place for breakfast...bringing the leftovers home for a second meal is an added bonus. Not only is the service personal, but the food is delicious. Although the menu can be a little more expensive than we'd like to spend on a Saturday morning, the meals are always satisfying. Not to mention the house-made apple cider and banana bread!!

data.title: Your best choice for breakfast
data.text: Always busy, but the team is always working hard to get you a table asap. Food is great and plentiful. You must try the banana bread. Great stop before jumping on the sounder train.

data.title: Plentiful breakfast...& lunch!
data.text: Trip Advisor led us here after a gas stop on our way to Mt. Rainer. Awesome! Friendly staff. Clean, nice. If you aren't a big eater, suggest you split a half-order! I had a half-order and could only eat half. The rest I had for lunch. Their banana bread is the best!

data.title: Too Much Food, Terrible Service
data.text: If you don't accept Amex, post a damned sign. Don't leave your incredibly lousy waitstaff to announce "We don't take that." How embarrassing. Too much food. No one finished their breakfast. You do know there are hungry people in this country, no? What a waste. Our waitress was the epitome of bad. Never came back with the promised coffee and spent 15 minutes talking to a regular while we waited for our check which she was supposed to bring right back.

data.title: Big Breakfast
data.text: You will NOT leave this place hungry. That being said it can be a challenge if you are in a hurry. You most likely will stand in line waiting for a table and getting your meal. This place has been an Auburn institution for ever and people want to come here for meals, especially Breakfast. The omelettes are huge as are the muffins. Good food and good choices.

data.title: Great breakfast
data.text: This place was a great choice, get there by 9am or you will have to stand in line for a while. If you have the offer of a half or whole, go with the half unless you want to take a lot of food home. I went with the half and only are half of it.

data.title: Excellent Service
data.text:
My wife and I spent the day in Auburn after returning from a cruise. We noticed that Sun Break was rated the best in the area, so we decided to give it a try. Being from the east coast, we were immediately taken back by how friendly and helpful the entire staff was. We were  helped by a very sweet young lady who offered some great suggestions. The sandwich's we're outstanding and my wife had nothing but great things to say about the soup. The young lady who helped us out at the counter. Stopped out to check on us and even brought some complimentary banana bread which was fantastic!
Sun break is definitely worth a visit.

data.title: Seemed over-hyped to me......
data.text:
We arrived and stood in line for at least a half hour. Not too horrible for one of the most well reviewed restaurant in town. We were then seated and waited again for a waitress to show up and take our drink order, which she forgot 33% of, aka we ordered 3 drinks and she only remembered 2. We then placed our food orders and relaxed for a little while. The place is very clean and is constantly buzzing.

I tried the biscuits and gravy, and was again sadly disappointed. First, the biscuits are large, flat, and square, as a southerner I thought someone was serving me cornbread, but nope they were 'biscuits'. Second, the gravy (for the second time in the PNW) had a yellow hue, not unlike chicken gravy and the bits of sausage I could see were pink. I choked down 1 whole 'biscuit' and could not stomach any more. DO NOT ORDER THIS ITEM. My wife had french toast that she enjoyed but the flavoring was so subtle it was non-existent. Even the syrup seemed flavorless. This trend continued to the sausage our daughter ordered, flavorless pork sausage - never heard of that before. My mother got an asparagus-hollandaise omelet that again lacked any substantial flavor.
Maybe we expected too much due to the hype, or maybe just pick the three items on the menu that are no good. I would give it one more shot and welcome recommendations for  soemthing to try that actually has flavor.

data.title: Birthday breakfast
data.text: This place is awesome!!!  The staff personal are friendly.  The amount of food is enough for two people and tastes delicious.

data.title: A terrific breakfast place!
data.text: This restaurant has great food along with great help.   The owner is usually around making sure that patrons are happy.

data.title: One of Auburns Best Breakfast/Lunch Restaurants
data.text:
Breakfast is good but be sure and order half order. Whole order would feed your whole family. A little on the pricey side. Usually a line to get seated. 
Lunch menu is basically soup/sandwiches/salads. Again unless you are really hungry a half sandwich with soup/salad will fill you up.
Friendly staff.
Closed Mondays

data.title: Best Breakfast in Auburn!!
data.text: The breakfast at Sunbreak is hands down the best one in the Auburn area and I would put it up against anything in King County.  Great food , HUGE portions, and a friendly staff.  They have been an Auburn favorite for decades and also donate to numerous charitable causes in the community.  Breakfasts aren't cheap, but I guarantee you will go home with leftovers...it's like two meals.

data.title: NOT Open Mondays
data.text:
The Sun Break Cafe is not open Mondays, as you'll see from the many signs on their building.  They want you to know this.  

This little restaurant is very popular and very expensive, neither of which is justified, in my opinion.  It's a lot of food of course but sometimes I'd like to just pay for the one meal I ordered, rather than the 2-3 meals they bring you.  Their food is what you'd expect from a breakfast place but of the three meals I've tried, none were over the top incredible.  If their prices were $3-$4 less I'd come here more often, but then the lines would be even longer, so maybe not.  I've never been there where there wasn't a line out the door, so they're clearly doing something right.  The service was quite friendly and the little store in the front is very cute and a nice diversion if you're lucky enough to have someone in your party hold your place in line while you browse.  Last time I was there, I browsed for about 10 minutes and when I came back the line hadn't moved at all, so we left.
